<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1684">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11 D 29/31.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 88.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 238,
                            of the 28th ultimo, in which you report that you have addressed a note
                            to the Panaman Foreign Office calling attention to the necessity of
                            apprehending those members of the national police force, who were guilty
                            of the unjustifiable assault upon American citizens on July 4 last, as
                            being an in <pb facs="1376" n="1260" xml:id="pg_1260"/> dispensable part
                            of any adjustment of the case between the two Governments.</p>
                        <p>Your action in the matter is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>